<h2>What to Expect After Submitting</h2>
<p>Set realistic expectations. <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/link-building-statistics/">Link building takes approximately 3.1 months</a> for noticeable ranking improvements.</p>
<p>Here is a rough timeline:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Week 1-2:</strong> Submit to Priority 1 sites. Profiles go live within 3-7 days.</li>
<li><strong>Month 1:</strong> Complete Priority 2 submissions. First referral traffic appears from SourceForge and AlternativeTo.</li>
<li><strong>Month 2-3:</strong> Google crawls and indexes your new backlinks. <a href="/blog/increase-organic-traffic/">Organic traffic</a> starts climbing.</li>
<li><strong>Month 3-4:</strong> Secondary effects kick in. Higher domain rating helps existing pages rank better. New referring domains compound over time.</li>
<li><strong>Month 6+:</strong> With 15+ review site profiles active and 50+ reviews collected, your brand entity becomes strongly established. AI search engines begin recommending your product in relevant queries.</li>
</ul>
<p>One important number: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/saas-link-building-statistics-usa-2025-eric-carrell-x6z0c">82% of high-ranking SaaS websites</a> have at least 1 backlink from a DA 70+ domain. Every Priority 1 and Priority 2 site on this list exceeds that threshold.</p>
<p>The ROI math is straightforward. The average paid backlink costs <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/link-building-statistics/">$83</a>. Listing on 14 dofollow review sites for free would cost $1,162 if you purchased equivalent links. The average guest post costs $609. These 105 free listings replace $14,000+ worth of paid link building. That is before counting the referral traffic, brand signals, and AI search visibility.</p>
<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>Are backlinks from software review sites valuable for SEO?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Review sites like G2 (DR 92), SourceForge (DR 92), and Capterra (DR 91) are among the highest-authority domains on the internet. A single backlink from a DR 80+ domain can <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/saas-link-building-statistics-usa-2025-eric-carrell-x6z0c">increase organic traffic by 12-18%</a> within 30-45 days. Directory backlinks also diversify your <a href="/blog/backlink-audit-guide/">backlink profile</a>, which Google rewards.</p>
<p><strong>Do software review sites give dofollow or nofollow backlinks?</strong></p>
<p>Both. Of the 23 sites listed here, 14 provide dofollow links and 9 provide nofollow links. G2, Capterra, SourceForge, Clutch, and AlternativeTo are among the dofollow sites. TrustRadius, Trustpilot, and Product Hunt use nofollow. Check the <a href="/blog/dofollow-vs-nofollow/">dofollow vs nofollow guide</a> for a full explanation of how each type affects rankings.</p>
<p><strong>How much does it cost to get listed on review sites?</strong></p>
<p>Most review sites offer free basic listings. G2, Capterra, SourceForge, AlternativeTo, SaaSHub, and FinancesOnline all accept free submissions. Paid options typically cover premium placement, analytics dashboards, and review generation tools. BetaList charges $129 for fast-track listing. Trustpilot charges for review invitation tools. You can build a strong backlink profile from review sites without spending anything.</p>
<p><strong>How long does it take for review site backlinks to impact rankings?</strong></p>
<p>Expect 2-4 months for measurable results. Google needs to crawl the review site, discover your link, and recalculate your domain's authority. <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/link-building-statistics/">Link building efforts take about 3.1 months</a> on average for noticeable impact. Submit to the highest-authority sites first to accelerate the timeline.</p>
<p><strong>Do review site listings help with AI search visibility?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. AI search engines like ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Google AI Overviews pull recommendations from high-authority review platforms. <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/link-building-statistics/">73.2% of SEO professionals</a> believe backlinks influence AI search results. Being listed on G2, Capterra, and Product Hunt increases the odds that AI assistants recommend your product when users ask for software suggestions.</p>
<p><strong>Should I focus on review sites or guest posting for backlinks?</strong></p>
<p>Do both. Review site listings are faster and cheaper. The average guest post costs <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/link-building-statistics/">$609</a>, while most review listings are free. Start with review sites for quick authority wins. Layer in <a href="/blog/guest-posting-guide/">guest posting</a> and <a href="/blog/resource-page-link-building/">resource page link building</a> for content-driven backlinks that complement your directory listings.</p>
